File: The president announced the number of deaths due to COVID-19 is currently at 1,672. PRETORIA - The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 80,412, President Cyril Ramaphosa said. The president addressed the nation on Wednesday about the regulations on dealing with the COVID-19 pandemic. Over one million tests have been conducted so far. READ: Hospital patients highest priority: Karim The president also announced the number of deaths is currently at 1,672. “The recoveries to date are 44,331. This translates to a recovery rate of about 55 percent,” the president said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.